    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-01-11T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-01-11T21:00:00-05:00" n="559"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/741: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-01-12T10:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1927—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 12—5:56 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>24. Your telegram number 251, October 28, noon.<note n="36" xml:id="d559fn36">
                        <ref target="frus1926v01#pg_1091">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 1091</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>I understand that Chinese Telegraph Administration is proposing to accept
                        invitation to conference at New York but that appointment of representative
                        has been delayed in consequence of disorganization in the Ministry of
                        Communication.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>My informant intimated that further reason for delay was perhaps fear or
                        unwillingness of the Chinese to commit themselves until the Japanese have
                        indicated willingness to participate.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Repeated to Tokyo as my number 2, January 11, 11 a.m.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
